<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F8922B258FF0DFAE0" author="Pallas, P. S." pageId="5" pageNumber="508" refId="ref24974" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1766) Miscellanea Zoologica. Petrum van Cleef, Hagae Comitum, 224 pp., 14 pls." type="book" year="1766">Pallas, 1766</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322DFC5281EFF8F8CB7B210FDB7FA10" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B878C4E281EFF8F8CB7B210FDB7FA10" blockId="5.[151,1437,1281,1740]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281EFF8F8CB7B210FE9DFABC" bold="true" box="[199,322,1353,1379]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Archinomins with body fusiform. Caruncle trilobate, medial lobe wide, plicate, lateral lobes narrow, plicate, tips tapered or blunt. Dorsal pigmentation patterns variable. Branchiae bipinnate in most chaetigers; a few anterior chaetigers with cirriform branchiae. Dorsal cirri with cirrophores. Anus terminal in last chaetigers; posterior end margin with a pair of cirriform lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C322DFC5281EFF8F8CB7B280FA92F913" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B878C4E281EFF8F8CB7B280FA92F913" blockId="5.[151,1437,1281,1740]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281EFF8F8CB7B280FEE4FA2C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1497,1523]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F8D33B280FDEDFA2B" author="Bruguiere, J. G." box="[323,562,1497,1524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" refId="ref21950" refString="Bruguiere, J. G. (1789) Encyclopedie Methodique: Histoire Naturelle des Vers. Tome I. Panckoucke, Paris, 758 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 53769" type="book" year="1789">Bruguière (1789: 45)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F7CD281EFF8F8E0FB280FCAEFA2C" authorityName="Bruguiere" authorityYear="1789" box="[639,881,1497,1523]" class="Polychaeta" family="Amphinomidae" genus="Amphinome" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphinomida" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="capillata">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281EFF8F8E0FB280FCAEFA2C" box="[639,881,1497,1523]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">Amphinome capillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new name for 
<taxonomicName id="4C38F7CD281EFF8F8822B280FA47FA2C" authority="Pallas, 1766" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1766" box="[1106,1432,1497,1523]" class="Polychaeta" family="Aphroditidae" genus="Aphrodita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="B94C505C281EFF8F8822B280FADCFA2C" box="[1106,1283,1497,1523]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">Aphrodita flava</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F897BB280FA47FA2C" author="Pallas, P. S." box="[1291,1432,1497,1523]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" refId="ref24974" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1766) Miscellanea Zoologica. Petrum van Cleef, Hagae Comitum, 224 pp., 14 pls." type="book" year="1766">Pallas, 1766</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, even from the original proposal, his species name is a junior synonym. It must be emphasized that although the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F8E65B178FD14F9E4" author="Pallas, P. S." box="[533,715,1569,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" refId="ref24974" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1766) Miscellanea Zoologica. Petrum van Cleef, Hagae Comitum, 224 pp., 14 pls." type="book" year="1766">Pallas, 1766: 97</bibRefCitation>
) and most other papers indicate this is an Indian Ocean species, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F8CE7B11CFE6DF9BF" author="De Blainville, H." box="[151,434,1605,1632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" pagination="365 - 625" refId="ref22370" refString="De Blainville, H. (1828) Vers (Entomoz.). Dictonnaire des Sciences Naturelles, 57, 365 - 625." type="journal article" year="1828">de Blainville (1828: 452)</bibRefCitation>
listed the then known synonyms, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F8F2FB11CFBE9F980" author="Fauvel, P." box="[863,1078,1605,1631]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" pagination="159 - 277" refId="ref22895" refString="Fauvel, P. (1917) Annelides Polychetes de l'Australie meridionale. Archives de Zoologie Experimentale et Generale, 56, 159 - 277." type="journal article" year="1917">Fauvel (1917: 190)</bibRefCitation>
updated the list. Regretfully, de Blainville indicated that “la seule espèce est de l’Amérique méridionale.” (the only species is from Central America). Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9F1BF281EFF8F8D40B1D4FDBFF978" author="De Quatrefages, A." box="[304,608,1677,1703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="508" refId="ref22395" refString="De Quatrefages, A. (1866) Histoire naturelle des Anneles marins et d'eau douce. Annelides et Gephyriens. Vol. 1. Librarie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 588 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 122818" type="book" year="1866">de Quatrefages (1866: 387)</bibRefCitation>
gave as its distribution the 
<collectingCountry id="F32FCCDE281EFF8F8FFDB1D4FC0FF978" box="[909,976,1677,1703]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="508">China</collectingCountry>
Seas, and following Fauvel’s conclusion, the species was regarded as having a very wide distribution including at least the Indian and Pacific oceans.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
